Here is a Python solution for the problem:

```python
def maximumCreatures(N, P, Q, A):
    # Initialize dp array to store the maximum number of creatures that can be paid with given coins
    dp = [0]*(N+1)

    # Base case when no creatures to pay or no coins
    for i in range(1, N+1):
        dp[i] = A[i-1]  # Store the extra amount paid by each creature

    # Fill the dp array using dynamic programming
    for coin in range(P+1):
        for i in range(coin, N+1):
            dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[i-coin] + A[i-1]//coin)

    for coin in range(2, Q+1):
        for i in range(coin, N+1):
            if (i - coin >= 0):
                dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[i-coin] + A[i-1]//coin)

    # The maximum number of creatures that can be paid back is the maximum value in the dp array
    return max(dp)

