Here is a step-by-step approach:

1. Initialize two variables, left and right, to track the current positions of the heads for the leftmost and rightmost tracks, respectively. Start both at infinity (INT_MAX).

2. Loop through the list of tracks to read (p_i) in ascending order. For each track, move the leftmost head (head_i) towards the current track if it hasn't visited it yet or if it is currently farthest from the current track among all heads that haven't visited the current track. If multiple such heads exist, move the one closest to the current track.

3. Update the left and right variables with the new positions of the leftmost and rightmost heads for the leftmost and rightmost tracks, respectively.

4. Repeat the loop until all tracks have been processed. If the left variable becomes smaller than the right variable, return the difference between the two variables multiplied by the number of heads. If not, return the sum of the absolute differences between the left variable and each track number.

