In the following steps, we will first implement a function that generates all possible combinations of $N$ digits using dynamic programming. After generating the combinations, we will iterate through them and check if the weight is equal to the given $W$. Finally, we will use a HashMap to store the counts of unique combinations modulo $10^9+7$ and return the result.

