Here's a Python implementation of the Ulam Sequence function:

```python
def ulam_sequence(u0, u1, n):
    sequence = [u0, u1]
    used = {u0: True, u1: True}

    while len(sequence) < n:
        next_term = float('inf')
        for i in range(len(sequence)):
            for j in range(i, len(sequence)):
                if (i != j and sequence[i] + sequence[j] not in used):
                    candidate = sequence[i] + sequence[j]
                    if candidate < next_term:
                        next_term = candidate
        sequence.append(next_term)
        used[next_term] = True

    return sequence[0:n]
```

