3. The while loop continues until the start and end pointers cross each other, meaning the array is properly partitioned with elements smaller than the pivot on the left and larger elements on the right.

4. We swap elements at start and end pointers to bring the partition closer to completion.

5. If end - 1 is the desired k-th largest, we return it. If it is greater than k, we recurse on the left subarray (elements smaller than pivot). If it is less than k, we recurse on the right subarray (elements greater than pivot).

